olive oil
¼ tsp salt
¼ onion
1 carrot
1 bag coriander
1 tsp white wine vinegar
1 packet Mango Mayonnaise
1 cucumber
1 bag salad leaves
8 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 sachet Mild Caribbean Jerk Seasoning
1 packet Beef Rump

• Place beef rump between 2 sheets of baking paper. Using a meat mallet or rolling pin, pound beef until slightly flattened (this tenderises the beef!). Season beef rump on both sides.
• In a medium bowl, combine mild Caribbean jerk seasoning, the salt and a drizzle of olive oil. Add beef and toss to coat. Set aside.
• Finely chop red onion (see ingredients). Grate carrot. Roughly chop coriander and cucumber.

• In a medium bowl, add carrot, onion, coriander and cucumber. Add a drizzle of olive oil and the white wine vinegar. Season with salt and pepper, then toss to combine and set aside.

TIP: Add less raw onion if you're not a fan!

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over a high heat. When oil is hot, cook beef, turning regularly, for 5-6 mins or until cooked to your liking (this will give you a medium steak).
• Transfer to a plate, cover and set aside to rest, 5 mins.
• Meanwhile, microwave mini flour tortillas on a plate for 10 second bursts, until warmed through.

• Slice beef.
• Fill tortillas with some mixed salad leaves and Caribbean beef.
• Top with cucumber salsa and mango mayonnaise to serve.